Guard `el->list == NULL` in lxb_html_document_event_destroy
=============================================================

LIB:     lexbor
TAG:     2.4.0
APPLY:   patch -p1 < this/file
TARGET:  source/lexbor/html/interfaces/document.c

Bug
---
`lxb_html_document_event_destroy` has three reachable paths but only
two are guarded. After `el->style != NULL` runs the AVL foreach to
tear down per-element cascade entries, control falls through to the
`destroy:` label which dereferences `el->list` unconditionally. For
elements that had no inline `style="..."` attribute — the common case
— `el->list` is NULL and the dereference segfaults.

Reproducer
----------
Create an element via `lxb_dom_document_create_element`, insert it
into the tree (so the ev_insert hook cascades any matching rules onto
`el->style`), then `lxb_dom_node_destroy_deep`. AffineUI's imm-mode
"clear and rebuild" path hits this on every rebuild after the first.

Path analysis (document.c around line 1193):

    if (el->style == NULL) {
        if (el->list != NULL) goto destroy;   // path A: list guaranteed non-NULL
        return LXB_STATUS_OK;                 // path B: nothing to do
    }
    // el->style != NULL — walk AVL to remove cascade entries
    status = lexbor_avl_foreach(...);
    if (status != LXB_STATUS_OK) return status;
    // FALL THROUGH — but el->list may still be NULL

    destroy:
        el->list->first = NULL;     // ← buggy on path C
        ...

Fix
---
Wrap the `destroy:` body in `if (el->list != NULL) { ... }`.

When upstream lands the fix
----------------------------
Delete this patch file. `scripts/fetch_deps.sh` will no longer
re-apply it on the next dependency refresh.

---
diff -u a/source/lexbor/html/interfaces/document.c b/source/lexbor/html/interfaces/document.c
--- a/source/lexbor/html/interfaces/document.c
+++ b/source/lexbor/html/interfaces/document.c
@@ -1212,11 +1212,15 @@

 destroy:

-    el->list->first = NULL;
-    el->list->last = NULL;
-
-    el->list = lxb_css_rule_declaration_list_destroy(el->list, true);
+    /* affineui patch: guard NULL list. Upstream falls through from
+     * the AVL-foreach branch above without checking that el->list is
+     * non-NULL. Elements with cascade-matched style but no inline
+     * `style="..."` attribute (the common case) segfault here.
+     */
+    if (el->list != NULL) {
+        el->list->first = NULL;
+        el->list->last = NULL;
+        el->list = lxb_css_rule_declaration_list_destroy(el->list, true);
+    }

     return LXB_STATUS_OK;
 }
